	  aaaauuuuttttooooccccoooonnnnffffiiiigggg is	a utility which	is run to add software to the
	  operating system when	new devices are	added.	It responds to
	  the following	flag options:


	  ----VVVV   Print the current version number	of ////eeeettttcccc////aaaauuuuttttooooccccoooonnnnffffiiiigggg.


	  ----IIII   Call device specific initialization routines for	all
	       modules included	in the new kernel.


	  ----vvvv   Verbose:	give a step-by-step account of the
	       autoconfiguration process.


	  ----kkkk   Patch the current running kernel	(currently not
	       implemented).


	  ----uuuu   Build a ////uuuunnnniiiixxxx file as output (also set by ----aaaa).


	  ----aaaa   Do the default autoconfig function if required (check
	       to see if the running kernel requires
	       autoconfiguration).  Build a kernel as output. Call
	       driver specific initialization routines.	(-Iu).


